{
  "uuid": "b260d5ec6f9eac70140a01b4b0da05b6",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Executive",
  "description": "<p>Join our team as a Sales Supervisor, where you will play a crucial role in expanding our customer base and ensuring client satisfaction. We are seeking an individual to fulfill the following roles and responsibilities:</p><p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>1. <strong>Customer Relations:</strong>Open new customer outlets and service existing ones for both new and recurring orders.</p><p>2. <strong>Sales Development:</strong>Develop and maximize sales with customers by building strong rapport and maintaining professional business relationships.</p><p>3. <strong>Product Distribution:</strong>Ensure efficient distribution of products to customers, optimizing performance.</p><p>4. <strong>Payment Management:</strong>Remind and collect outstanding payments/bills when necessary.</p><p>5. <strong>Sales Performance Reporting:</strong>Generate general reports on sales performance within your portfolio, providing insights to the company.</p><p>6. <strong>Ad-hoc Duties:</strong>Undertake ad-hoc duties as per customer or management requests.</p><p>7. <strong>Growth Strategies:</strong>Develop growth strategies and business acquisition plans to increase the client base, achieving Key Performance Indicators (KPIs).</p><p>8. <strong>Market Analysis:</strong>Identify trends and customer needs, building a short/medium/long-term sales pipeline in accordance with KPIs.</p><p>9. <strong>Marketing Coordination:</strong>Assist in the coordination and implementation of marketing strategies, delegating tasks that align with strategic goals.</p><p>10. <strong>Relationship Building:</strong>Establish strong relationships and collaborate closely with brand owners.</p><p>11. <strong>Client Onboarding:</strong>Onboard new clients using company apps for seamless ordering.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Proven experience in sales or a related field.</p><p>· Excellent interpersonal and communication skills.</p><p>· Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities.</p><p>· Results-driven with a focus on achieving KPIs.</p><p>· Ability to identify trends and customer needs for strategic planning.</p><p>· Familiarity with marketing strategies and implementation.</p><p>· Proficient in using company apps for client onboarding and order processing.</p><p>We thank you for your interest, and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
